cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a generative model based on a conditional variational autoencoder for de novo molecular design. This involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the manipulation of multiple molecular properties, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of molecular structures and properties also suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
